<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1949&amp;p=15299#p15299"><![CDATA[
Here you go <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /> <br />I never added caption text to a skin script before, so was a head scratcher.<br />I made the simple stretched caption area, and decided to push it some more, <br />as I got some free time away from work.<br /><br />So there are 3 slightly different variation caption areas.<br />Flat extension, flat with trench edge, and a curvy classy &quot;crown molding&quot; type.<br /><br />Don't think I can ever get that nice sheen, like on the right side.<br />That was made by fluke. Hope I can make more of those splicing mistakes in future <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /> <br /><br />Best to go to those artists over on Deviant for more CSM menus. <br />I came across ones posted there, but not here.<br /><br />Oh shizzlenits, the &quot; add left edge&quot; radio buttons just locked up on me<br />...reset skin, restarted CSM, seems ok now? If other users get same issue, let it be known.<br />Either I missed something, bug, or full moon!<br />bye<br /><br />Back again. I made a minor change to Main opacity. <br />Changed from alpha to region. That way, menu shadow can be used, with out the line above.<br /><br />Just tried on Win7. No button lockup <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Fri Oct 17, 2014 4:09 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
