<author><name><![CDATA[juniper7]]></name></author>
<updated>2014-01-01T17:24:01-07:00</updated>
<published>2014-01-01T17:24:01-07:00</published>
<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1949&amp;p=9833#p9833</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1949&amp;p=9833#p9833"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Experiment #3 Carbon Steps]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1949&amp;p=9833#p9833"><![CDATA[
Experiment #3 Carbon Steps<br /><br />This skin still has the bars from work. <br />I modified the XP lookalike skin of CSM, with a chainsaw. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_twisted.gif" alt=":twisted:" title="Twisted Evil" /> <br />I made it as plain as can be. No bright Windows colors.<br />I made this one to follow the Win 8 glass color, but only for selection.<br />It more or less tracks the desktop background color, <br />just at differing levels of brightness.<br /><br />I tried briefly in Win 7. It shows up a menu shadow artifact line, <br />above top right corner.<br />Something does not like the way I cut right column down a bit? <br />To get rid of the line, disable the &quot;menu shadow&quot; in the &quot;Menu look&quot; tab.<br />Also in Win7, the selection color stays grey, always <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_sad.gif" alt=":(" title="Sad" /><br /><br />Tried with CSM 4.0.2 on Win7/8 Works best in Win8. <br />Not compatible with most older versions of CSM. Will only partially work.<br />After downloading file, paste in skins folder. Exit CSM, restart CSM, <br />and go to &quot;Start Menu Style&quot; tab. Pick Classic or Classic two columns.<br />Pick &quot;Carbon Steps&quot; in Skin tab. <br /><br />ps. Feel free to change anything in this skin, especially my errors, <br />as it's just an experiment.<br />Sometimes errors can lead to new ideas. When I accidently put the wrong figures for slices for single column, <br />it squeezed the edge up. This made the 3D depth appear shorter.<br />It worked for single, but not 2 column, so I made screen shot bitmaps of it all instead. <br />Nothing is permanent, everything changes:)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Wed Jan 01, 2014 5:24 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
